sql:
ALTER TABLE bookings
ADD service VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
ADD sub_service VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
ADD phone VARCHAR(20) NOT NULL,
ADD message TEXT,
ADD price DECIMAL(10,2) NOT NULL,
ADD payment_status ENUM('pending', 'paid') DEFAULT 'pending';




Step-by-Step Guidelines: Building the PHP Calendar Booking Service
This is a concise recap of our journey from scratch. Refer back if you forgetâ€”copy it to a note!
1. Setup Environment (XAMPP)

Download/install XAMPP (free web server with PHP/MySQL).
Start Apache & MySQL in XAMPP Control Panel.
Create project folder: C:\xampp\htdocs\calendar-service (or equivalent on Mac/Linux).
Test: Open http://localhost in browser (should show XAMPP dashboard).

2. Create Database

Open phpMyAdmin: http://localhost/phpmyadmin.
Create DB: Name it bookingcalendar.
Run SQL to create bookings table (copy from early responses: includes id, name, email, date, timeslot, etc.).
Later updates: Add columns like service, sub_service, phone, message, price, payment_status via ALTER TABLE.

3. Core Files & Code

config.php: Database connection, service definitions (e.g., hair cuts with subs, durations, prices), time slot function, PayPal/email settings.
index.php: Main appâ€”handles services menu, sub-services, calendar, slots, form, PayPal button.
Use Bootstrap for UI.
Logic: GET params for service/sub/date; POST for booking form.

success.php: Handles post-paymentâ€”saves booking, sends emails (admin & customer) via PHPMailer.
dashboard.php: Admin viewâ€”password-protected (admin123â€”change it!), shows bookings table.

4. Key Features Added Step-by-Step

Basic Calendar: Monthly grid, click date â†’ show slots (green available, red booked).
Services Menu: Cards with images, "MORE INFO" â†’ sub-services list â†’ "BOOK NOW" â†’ calendar (custom durations).
Booking Form: After slot selectâ€”name, email, phone, optional message. Validates input.
PayPal Integration: Sandbox setup (developer.paypal.com). After form â†’ PayPal button â†’ redirect to success.php on payment.
Emails: PHPMailer for reliable sending (SMTP setup with Gmail). Admin notification + customer confirmation (HTML templates).
Past Slots: On today's date, grey/blur "Closed" for passed times (compare current time).
Dashboard: View all bookings; login with password.

5. Testing & Access

Run app: http://localhost/calendar-service/index.php.
Dashboard: http://localhost/calendar-service/dashboard.php (login: admin123).
Database: http://localhost/phpmyadmin â†’ select bookingcalendar â†’ browse bookings table.
Test bookings: Select service â†’ sub â†’ date â†’ slot â†’ form â†’ pay (sandbox) â†’ check emails/DB.

6. Customization & Tips

Edit services/prices in config.php.
Change PayPal to live (replace client ID).
Security: Add HTTPS, CAPTCHA, real auth for production.
Debug: Enable errors in PHP (add ini_set('display_errors', 1); at file top).
Deploy: Upload to web host (e.g., Hostinger), import DB.

